I think the use cases where one needs to use previously defined attributes can be (and probably should be, TOWTDI) solved by ``__post_init__``, for example:
```python
@dataclass
class C:
    x: int
    y: int
    coords: List[int] = None  # just a placeholder

    def __post_init__(self):
        self.coords = [self.x, self.y]
```

