Looks good to me, except for the frozen mechanism.

I assume you made _frozen a class var in order to freeze the config and all its nested configs, but freeze actually sets an object specific var, it doesn't affect the nested ones. You can test it e.g. by setting `config2.encoder.max_seq_len = 10` after freezing, it will happily set the new value. We can set the class variable as `Config._frozen = True`. But this will also freeze independent configs, not elegant and may be problematic in the future. Or we can make _frozen a normal attribute and freeze recursively:

```
    def freeze(self):
        self._frozen = True
        for v in self.__dict__.values():
            if isinstance(v, Config):
                v.freeze()
```

