@palango This looks like the right solution. If I understand you correctly you want the debug log to always include *every* debug log from all loggers but still allow the user to configure the console logging as usual.

The reason it doesn't is that we set the level on the nested loggers based on the user config and once a level has been set messages below that level aren't propagated up the chain.

A possible way around that could be to not set the levels on the individual loggers but instead add a structlog processor that filters the log records according to the user config just before passing them to the `StreamHandler` (and not include that processor for the debug log).

